Contact Email: museum@capistranohistory.org

Contact Person: Jan Siegel

Latino Materials: Newspapers, Photographs, Artifacts, Books, Pamphlets, Newsletters, Audio Visual, Manuscripts, structures

Details: Mission town founded by St. Junipero Serra, 7th in California Mission chain. The museum has thousands of photographs and hundreds of artifacts, books, pamphlets, etc. The museum is located on the oldest residential street in California. The house ha spassed from generation to generation and the current owner's children are the 10th generation living in the place. The family is of Hispanic descent. They are currently preserving an adobe house from 1840 in their property, built by an Hispanic, that will be used to highlight artifacts of the Mexican period in California. Hispanic culture is the core of this community. Spanish, Mexican, Basque have all played an integral part of their history.
Location:
31831 Los Rios Street
 San Juan Capistrano, CA 92675
